p2
VThematic presentation
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe Sri Guruguha Gana Saba, Srirangam, conducted its December monthly music programme in a unique manner recently.The performers &#8211; Srinidhi, Sudha, Yogitha Desikan, Ramya, Swetha, Iswarya, Sriram and Ranjitha (students of Shyamala Rangarajan), Nivetha and Keerthi (students of L. Saraswathi) &#8211; chose the immortal works of the great poet, Sri Subramaya Bharati and rendered them in Carnatic ragas. The songs were presented under three themes &#8211; Gnanam (Enlightenment), Sakthi and Desabhakthi (Patriotism). The singers were accompanied by Anand and Aditya (violin) and Uthamarkoil S. Hariprasad (mridangam).Pankajam, who presided over the function distributed certificates and laminated portraits of the poet to all the participants. She also suggested that the Sabha conducts competition on Bharatiar songs from  next year.
